    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1931-11-04T12:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1931-11-04T12:00:00-05:00" n="493"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d493">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">551.5G1/13: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Dawes</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Extract—Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-11-04T17:00:00+00:00"
                            >November 4, 1931—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received November 4—4:25 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>429.</p>
                <p rend="center">. . . . . . . . . . . . . .</p>
                <p>With reference to the proposal for a conference on silver, Mr. MacDonald
                    manifested a prejudice against the calling of any conference in which the views
                    of Great Britain did not coincide with those of the United States.</p>
                <p rend="center">. . . . . . . . . . . . . .</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Dawes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
